und md:text-base">6.1″ Liquid Retina LCD, 828 × 1792 px</p></div></div><div class="group flex items-start gap-3.5 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg"><span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-cpu h-5 w-5 text-primary/80"><rect width="16" height="16" x="4" y="4" rx="2"></rect><rect width="6" height="6" x="9" y="9" rx="1"></rect><path d="M15 2v2"></path><path d="M15 20v2"></path><path d="M2 15h2"></path><path d="M2 9h2"></path><path d="M20 15h2"></path><path d="M20 9h2"></path><path d="M9 2v2"></path><path d="M9 20v2"></path></svg></span><div><p class="mb-1 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Processor</p><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:text-base">A12 Bionic</p></div></div><div class="group flex items-start gap-3.5 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg"><span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-shield-check h-5 w-5 text-primary/80"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></span><div><p class="mb-1 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Latest Major iOS</p><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:text-base">iOS 18 (does not support iOS 26)</p></div></div></div><div class="group flex items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-border border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-card p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg"><span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-lightbulb h-5 w-5 text-primary/80"><path d="M15 14c.2-1 .7-1.7 1.5-2.5 1-.9 1.5-2.2 1.5-3.5A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .2 2.2 1.5 3.5.7.7 1.3 1.5 1.5 2.5"></path><path d="M9 18h6"></path><path d="M10 22h4"></path></svg></span><div><p class="mb-1 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Typical Use Case Today</p><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:text-base">Secondary phone, kids' device, budget daily driver for messaging and browsing</p></div></div></div></div></section><section id="ios-support" class="border-t border-border py-10 md:py-14"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">iPhone XR iOS Support Status in 2026</h2><div class="prose-device text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2 hover:[&amp;_a]:text-primary/80 [&amp;_ul]:list-disc [&amp;_ul]:pl-5 [&amp;_ul]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ul]:mt-3 [&amp;_ol]:list-decimal [&amp;_ol]:pl-5 [&amp;_ol]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ol]:mt-3 [&amp;_p]:mb-4 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0">
      <p>The iPhone XR shipped with iOS 12 and received major updates through iOS 18. As of 2026, it does not support iOS 26 and will not receive future major feature updates from Apple.</p>
      <p>Apple has historically provided limited security patches to devices one or two generations behind the current release. However, these patches are not guaranteed and typically address only critical vulnerabilities — they do not include new features or app framework updates.</p>
    </div><div class="mt-8"><h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">What iOS Version Does the iPhone XR Support?</h3><div class="prose-device text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2 hover:[&amp;_a]:text-primary/80 [&amp;_ul]:list-disc [&amp;_ul]:pl-5 [&amp;_ul]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ul]:mt-3 [&amp;_ol]:list-decimal [&amp;_ol]:pl-5 [&amp;_ol]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ol]:mt-3 [&amp;_p]:mb-4 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0">
        <p>The iPhone XR supports up to <strong>iOS 18</strong>. This was the last major iOS version available for the A12 Bionic chip. The device did not receive iOS 19, iOS 20, or any subsequent releases.</p>
        <p>It's important to understand the difference between <strong>feature updates</strong> and <strong>security updates</strong>:</p>
        </div><div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2"><div class="rounded-xl border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50/60 p-6 dark:border-blue-900/40 dark:bg-blue-950/20"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-100 p-2 text-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-900/40 dark:text-blue-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5"><path d="M9.937 15.5A2 2 0 0 0 8.5 14.063l-6.135-1.582a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.962L8.5 9.936A2 2 0 0 0 9.937 8.5l1.582-6.135a.5.5 0 0 1 .963 0L14.063 8.5A2 2 0 0 0 15.5 9.937l6.135 1.581a.5.5 0 0 1 0 .964L15.5 14.063a2 2 0 0 0-1.437 1.437l-1.582 6.135a.5.5 0 0 1-.963 0z"></path><path d="M20 3v4"></path><path d="M22 5h-4"></path><path d="M4 17v2"></path><path d="M5 18H3"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-base font-bold text-foreground">Feature Updates</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Major iOS releases (e.g., iOS 18 → iOS 19) bring new capabilities, app frameworks, and UI changes. The iPhone XR no longer receives these.</p></div><div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/60 p-6 dark:border-emerald-900/40 dark:bg-emerald-950/20"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 p-2 text-emerald-600 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 dark:text-emerald-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-shield-check h-5 w-5"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-base font-bold text-foreground">Security Updates</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Smaller patches that fix vulnerabilities. Apple may still issue these for iOS 18, but on a limited and unpredictable schedule.</p></div></div><div class="mt-4">
        <p>Sources: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/guide/iphone/iphe3fa5df43/ios" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple – iPhone models compatible with iOS</a></p>
      </div></div></div></section><section id="update-deprecation" class="border-t border-border py-10 md:py-14"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">What Happens When the iPhone XR Stops Getting iOS Updates?</h2><div class="prose-device text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2 hover:[&amp;_a]:text-primary/80 [&amp;_ul]:list-disc [&amp;_ul]:pl-5 [&amp;_ul]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ul]:mt-3 [&amp;_ol]:list-decimal [&amp;_ol]:pl-5 [&amp;_ol]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ol]:mt-3 [&amp;_p]:mb-4 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0">
      <p>The iPhone XR does not stop working when it loses iOS support. Calls, messaging, browsing, and most currently installed apps continue to function normally.</p>
      <p>What changes over time is <strong>app compatibility</strong>. App developers build against the latest iOS SDKs, and older versions gradually lose support. This process is gradual — not immediate — but accelerates as the device falls further behind the current iOS release.</p>
      <p>Security is the other consideration. Without regular patches, known vulnerabilities remain unaddressed. For most users, this doesn't create an immediate crisis, but it does increase risk over time — particularly for devices used for banking, payments, or storing sensitive information.</p>
    </div><div class="mt-8 space-y-0"><h3 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold">How Support Gradually Declines</h3><div class="relative border-l-2 border-border pl-8 space-y-8"><div class="relative"><div class="absolute -left-[2.55rem] top-0.5 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full p-1.5 bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-600 dark:bg-yellow-900/30 dark:text-yellow-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-circle-x h-5 w-5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="m15 9-6 6"></path><path d="m9 9 6 6"></path></svg></div><h4 class="text-base font-bold text-foreground">Major iOS Updates Stop</h4><p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">The device stops receiving new iOS versions. Existing apps and features continue to work normally.</p></div><div class="relative"><div class="absolute -left-[2.55rem] top-0.5 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full p-1.5 bg-orange-100 text-orange-600 dark:bg-orange-900/30 dark:text-orange-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-triangle-alert h-5 w-5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3"></path><path d="M12 9v4"></path><path d="M12 17h.01"></path></svg></div><h4 class="text-base font-bold text-foreground">Developer SDKs Move Forward</h4><p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">App developers build against newer iOS SDKs. Updates for older OS versions become less frequent, then stop.</p></div><div class="relative"><div class="absolute -left-[2.55rem] top-0.5 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full p-1.5 bg-red-100 text-destructive dark:bg-red-900/30"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-shield-check h-5 w-5"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></div><h4 class="text-base font-bold text-foreground">Security Patches Become Rare</h4><p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Apple may issue limited security patches, but on an unpredictable schedule. Known vulnerabilities remain unaddressed longer.</p></div></div></div><div class="mt-10"><h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">App Compatibility Issues Canadian Users May Notice</h3><p class="mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">From our experience, these are the categories of apps where Canadian users on the iPhone XR tend to notice compatibility issues first:</p><div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2"><div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg p-2 bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-900/30 dark:text-blue-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-banknote h-5 w-5"><rect width="20" height="12" x="2" y="6" rx="2"></rect><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"></circle><path d="M6 12h.01M18 12h.01"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Banking Apps</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">TD, RBC, Scotiabank, and BMO typically require iOS versions within two major releases of the current version.</p></div><div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg p-2 bg-purple-100 text-purple-600 dark:bg-purple-900/30 dark:text-purple-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-bus h-5 w-5"><path d="M8 6v6"></path><path d="M15 6v6"></path><path d="M2 12h19.6"></path><path d="M18 18h3s.5-1.7.8-2.8c.1-.4.2-.8.2-1.2 0-.4-.1-.8-.2-1.2l-1.4-5C20.1 6.8 19.1 6 18 6H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v10h3"></path><circle cx="7" cy="18" r="2"></circle><path d="M9 18h5"></path><circle cx="16" cy="18" r="2"></circle></svg></span><h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Transit &amp; Payment</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Presto, city transit apps, and mobile payment platforms often follow similar requirements.</p></div><div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg p-2 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-600 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 dark:text-emerald-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-building h-5 w-5"><rect width="16" height="20" x="4" y="2" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M9 22v-4h6v4"></path><path d="M8 6h.01"></path><path d="M16 6h.01"></path><path d="M12 6h.01"></path><path d="M12 10h.01"></path><path d="M12 14h.01"></path><path d="M16 10h.01"></path><path d="M16 14h.01"></path><path d="M8 10h.01"></path><path d="M8 14h.01"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Government Services</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">CRA My Account, provincial health apps, and digital ID services may require newer iOS versions for security compliance.</p></div><div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg p-2 bg-amber-100 text-amber-600 dark:bg-amber-900/30 dark:text-amber-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-lock-keyhole h-5 w-5"><circle cx="12" cy="16" r="1"></circle><rect x="3" y="10" width="18" height="12" rx="2"></rect><path d="M7 10V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v3"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-foreground">Two-Factor Auth</h4></div><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Microsoft Authenticator and Google Authenticator will eventually require newer OS versions.</p></div></div><p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">This doesn't mean these apps stop working overnight. The transition is gradual, and many apps continue to function on older iOS versions even after they stop receiving updates for them.</p></div></div></section><section id="worth-fixing" class="border-t border-border bg-secondary/20 py-14 md:py-20"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4"><div class="mb-10 max-w-2xl"><h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Is the iPhone XR Worth Fixing in 2026?</h2><div class="prose-device text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2 hover:[&amp;_a]:text-primary/80 [&amp;_ul]:list-disc [&amp;_ul]:pl-5 [&amp;_ul]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ul]:mt-3 [&amp;_ol]:list-decimal [&amp;_ol]:pl-5 [&amp;_ol]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ol]:mt-3 [&amp;_p]:mb-4 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0">
      <p>From our experience repairing iPhones daily, whether an iPhone XR is worth fixing depends on the type and extent of the damage. A single-issue repair on an otherwise functional device is often worthwhile. Multiple simultaneous failures typically tip the equation toward replacement.</p>
    </div></div><div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3"><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-border border-t-4 border-t-emerald-500 bg-card shadow-sm"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-xl bg-emerald-50/40 px-6 pt-6 pb-4 dark:bg-emerald-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-emerald-100 p-2.5 text-emerald-600 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 dark:text-emerald-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-wrench h-6 w-6"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"></path></svg></span><div><span class="mb-1 inline-block rounded-full bg-emerald-100 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-700 dark:bg-emerald-900/50 dark:text-emerald-300">Recommended</span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">When Repairing an iPhone XR Usually Makes Sense</h3></div></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-4"><div class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_li]:mb-2 [&amp;_strong]:text-foreground">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Battery replacement only</strong> — The most cost-effective repair for the XR. Restores daily battery life and removes performance throttling. Typically completed in under an hour.</li>
          <li><strong>Screen replacement only</strong> — If the display is cracked but everything else works (Face ID, cameras, charging), screen repair extends the device's life at a fraction of replacement cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Device otherwise in good condition</strong> — If the XR's software limitations aren't a problem for your use case (e.g., secondary phone, kids' device, basic daily driver), a single repair is usually worthwhile.</li>
        </ul>
      </div><a href="https://shop.mobiletechlab.ca/pages/repair2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-5 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-600 px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-emerald-700"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-wrench h-4 w-4"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"></path></svg>Book Repair</a></div></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-border border-t-4 border-t-amber-500 bg-card shadow-sm"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-xl bg-amber-50/40 px-6 pt-6 pb-4 dark:bg-amber-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-amber-100 p-2.5 text-amber-600 dark:bg-amber-900/40 dark:text-amber-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-arrow-up-right h-6 w-6"><path d="M7 7h10v10"></path><path d="M7 17 17 7"></path></svg></span><div><span class="mb-1 inline-block rounded-full bg-amber-100 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 dark:bg-amber-900/50 dark:text-amber-300">Consider Trade-In</span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">When It's Often Better to Sell or Upgrade Instead</h3></div></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-4"><div class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_li]:mb-2 [&amp;_strong]:text-foreground">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Screen + back glass damage</strong> — Combined repair cost for both panels on the XR often approaches or exceeds the device's market value.</li>
          <li><strong>Multiple major repairs required</strong> — Screen, battery, and charging port failures together make repair uneconomical in most cases.</li>
          <li><strong>Repair cost approaches device value</strong> — As a general guideline, if the total repair estimate exceeds 60–70% of what a comparable replacement costs, upgrading is usually the better investment.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For a full list of iPhone repair services we offer, see our <a href="/repair/iphone">iPhone repair page</a>.</p>
      </div><a class="mt-5 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-amber-300 bg-amber-50 px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-amber-700 transition-colors hover:bg-amber-100 dark:border-amber-800 dark:bg-amber-950/30 dark:text-amber-300 dark:hover:bg-amber-950/50" href="/trade-in"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-arrow-up-right h-4 w-4"><path d="M7 7h10v10"></path><path d="M7 17 17 7"></path></svg>View Upgrades</a></div></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-border border-t-4 border-t-blue-500 bg-card shadow-sm"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-xl bg-blue-50/40 px-6 pt-6 pb-4 dark:bg-blue-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-blue-100 p-2.5 text-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-900/40 dark:text-blue-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-database h-6 w-6"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse><path d="M3 5V19A9 3 0 0 0 21 19V5"></path><path d="M3 12A9 3 0 0 0 21 12"></path></svg></span><div><span class="mb-1 inline-block rounded-full bg-blue-100 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-900/50 dark:text-blue-300">Priority Service</span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Data-Critical Device</h3></div></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-4"><p class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">If the device contains irreplaceable photos, contacts, or documents, prioritize data extraction before making a repair-or-replace decision. We offer motherboard-level recovery for devices that won't power on.</p><a href="sms:2045009757" class="mt-5 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-blue-300 bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-blue-700 transition-colors hover:bg-blue-100 dark:border-blue-800 dark:bg-blue-950/30 dark:text-blue-300 dark:hover:bg-blue-950/50"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-database h-4 w-4"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse><path d="M3 5V19A9 3 0 0 0 21 19V5"></path><path d="M3 12A9 3 0 0 0 21 12"></path></svg>Contact for Data Recovery</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="common-damage" class="border-t border-border py-14 md:py-20"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-10 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Common iPhone XR Damage and What It Means</h2><div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2"><div class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border border-t-4 border-t-foreground/80 bg-card shadow-sm"><div class="px-6 pt-6 pb-4"><div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-secondary p-2.5 text-foreground/70"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-scan-eye h-6 w-6"><path d="M3 7V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h2"></path><path d="M17 3h2a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"></path><path d="M21 17v2a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-2"></path><path d="M7 21H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-2"></path><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><path d="M18.944 12.33a1 1 0 0 0 0-.66 7.5 7.5 0 0 0-13.888 0 1 1 0 0 0 0 .66 7.5 7.5 0 0 0 13.888 0"></path></svg></span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Front Glass Damage</h3></div><img src="/assets/iphone-xr-front-damage-D66yFWud.jpg" alt="iPhone XR with cracked front display glass, a common repair scenario" class="mb-4 w-full rounded-lg object-cover" loading="lazy"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        <p>Front glass damage is the most common repair we see on the iPhone XR. The XR uses a single LCD and digitizer assembly, which means the entire front panel is replaced as one unit. This keeps repair straightforward and turnaround fast.</p></div></div><div class="mt-auto px-6 pb-6"><div class="flex gap-3 rounded-xl bg-secondary/60 p-4"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-info mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-primary"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M12 16v-4"></path><path d="M12 8h.01"></path></svg><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Pro Tip:</span> Aftermarket OLED panels are available at lower price points than OEM, though colour accuracy and brightness may differ slightly. From our experience, most users find aftermarket OLED replacements acceptable for daily use.</p></div></div></div><div class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border border-t-4 border-t-foreground/80 bg-card shadow-sm"><div class="px-6 pt-6 pb-4"><div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-secondary p-2.5 text-foreground/70"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-layers h-6 w-6"><path d="m12.83 2.18a2 2 0 0 0-1.66 0L2.6 6.08a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.83l8.58 3.91a2 2 0 0 0 1.66 0l8.58-3.9a1 1 0 0 0 0-1.83Z"></path><path d="m22 17.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 17.65"></path><path d="m22 12.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 12.65"></path></svg></span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Back Glass Damage</h3></div><img src="/assets/iphone-xr-back-damage-vV6LEb6F.png" alt="iPhone XR with cracked back glass, a common repair scenario when evaluating whether the device is worth fixing" class="mb-4 w-full rounded-lg object-cover" loading="lazy"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline">
        <p>The repair is still viable and something we perform regularly, but it costs more than a screen replacement due to the additional labour. For devices with back glass damage only, repair is usually worthwhile. For devices with both front and back glass damage, the combined cost should be weighed against the device's current value.</p></div></div><div class="mt-auto px-6 pb-6"><div class="flex gap-3 rounded-xl bg-secondary/60 p-4"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-info mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-primary"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M12 16v-4"></path><path d="M12 8h.01"></path></svg><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Pro Tip:</span> The back glass is laser-welded to the stainless steel housing. Repair requires either a full housing swap or careful glass-only removal — a specialist procedure we perform regularly.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="trade-in-upgrade" class="border-t border-border py-14 md:py-20"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Trading In or Upgrading From an iPhone XR</h2><div class="mb-10 max-w-2xl text-muted-foreground">
      <p>The iPhone XR's trade-in value in 2026 is modest and heavily condition-dependent. Devices in good cosmetic condition with healthy batteries command higher values, while those with cracked screens, battery degradation, or carrier locks trade at significant discounts.</p>
      <p>If you're considering a trade-in, it's worth understanding the difference between <strong>cash trade-ins</strong> and <strong>store credit</strong>. Cash offers are typically lower but provide immediate liquidity. Store credit toward a replacement device is often higher but locks you into a specific retailer or carrier.</p>
      <p>Upgrading is optional and entirely user-led. For users whose daily needs are met by the XR, there's no urgency to upgrade. For those hitting app compatibility walls or needing better camera performance, common upgrade paths include:</p>
      </div><div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3"><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><span class="mb-1 inline-block w-fit rounded-full bg-primary/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-primary">Modern Performance</span><div class="mb-4 mt-3 flex items-center gap-3"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-secondary p-2.5 text-foreground/70"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-smartphone h-6 w-6"><rect width="14" height="20" x="5" y="2" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M12 18h.01"></path></svg></span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">iPhone 12</h3></div><p class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">First iPhone with 5G, MagSafe, and a significantly longer iOS support window. A natural upgrade for iPhone XR users who want continued software support.</p></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><span class="mb-1 inline-block w-fit rounded-full bg-emerald-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">Budget Friendly</span><div class="mb-4 mt-3 flex items-center gap-3"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-secondary p-2.5 text-foreground/70"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-shield-check h-6 w-6"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Certified Pre-Owned iPhone 12</h3></div><p class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Strong mid-range value for users buying used. Certified quality with warranty coverage.</p><a href="https://shop.mobiletechlab.ca/products/iphone-12" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-5 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-secondary px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/80">Shop Pre-Owned<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-arrow-right h-4 w-4"><path d="M5 12h14"></path><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path></svg></a></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"><span class="mb-1 inline-block w-fit rounded-full bg-amber-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">Max Screen Real Estate</span><div class="mb-4 mt-3 flex items-center gap-3"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-secondary p-2.5 text-foreground/70"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize h-6 w-6"><path d="M8 3H5a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v3"></path><path d="M21 8V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-3"></path><path d="M3 16v3a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h3"></path><path d="M16 21h3a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-3"></path></svg></span><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">iPhone 12/13 Pro Max</h3></div><p class="flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">For users who want to maintain the large-screen experience with modern camera and battery improvements.</p></div></div><div class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-sm text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline">
      <p>For current trade-in values based on your device's specific condition, see our <a href="/trade-in">trade-in page</a>.</p>
    </div></div></section><section id="decision-guide" class="border-t border-border bg-secondary/20 py-14 md:py-20"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4"><div class="mb-10 max-w-2xl"><h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Should You Keep, Fix, or Upgrade Your iPhone XR?</h2><div class="prose-device text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2 hover:[&amp;_a]:text-primary/80 [&amp;_ul]:list-disc [&amp;_ul]:pl-5 [&amp;_ul]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ul]:mt-3 [&amp;_ol]:list-decimal [&amp;_ol]:pl-5 [&amp;_ol]:space-y-1 [&amp;_ol]:mt-3 [&amp;_p]:mb-4 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0">
      <p>Based on your situation, repairing, trading in, or upgrading may make sense. Here's a practical framework based on common scenarios we see:</p>
    </div></div><div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3"><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md border-t-4 border-t-emerald-500"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-2xl px-6 pt-6 pb-4 bg-emerald-50/40 dark:bg-emerald-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-600 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 dark:text-emerald-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-wrench h-6 w-6"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Repair is Worthwhile</h4></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-3"><p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground/80">Still usable?</p><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Yes, with limitations. The iPhone XR handles messaging, browsing, email, and most social media without issue. Performance-intensive apps and newer games may struggle. Banking and government apps may begin requiring newer iOS versions.</p></div></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md border-t-4 border-t-amber-500"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-2xl px-6 pt-6 pb-4 bg-amber-50/40 dark:bg-amber-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-amber-100 text-amber-600 dark:bg-amber-900/40 dark:text-amber-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-arrow-up-right h-6 w-6"><path d="M7 7h10v10"></path><path d="M7 17 17 7"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Trade-In &amp; Upgrade</h4></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-3"><p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground/80">Worth fixing?</p><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Depends on damage. Single-issue repairs (battery or screen alone) are typically worthwhile. Multiple simultaneous repairs often exceed the device's value. Compare total repair cost against replacement options before deciding.</p></div></div><div class="flex h-full flex-col rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md border-t-4 border-t-blue-500"><div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-t-2xl px-6 pt-6 pb-4 bg-blue-50/40 dark:bg-blue-950/20"><span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-900/40 dark:text-blue-400"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-database h-6 w-6"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse><path d="M3 5V19A9 3 0 0 0 21 19V5"></path><path d="M3 12A9 3 0 0 0 21 12"></path></svg></span><h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">Data Recovery First</h4></div><div class="flex flex-1 flex-col px-6 pb-6 pt-3"><p class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground/80">Best long-term value?</p><p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Often trade-in plus upgrade. If you're hitting software limitations or need a device that will remain supported for 3+ more years, trading in the XR toward a newer model usually offers the best long-term value per dollar spent.</p></div></div></div><p class="mt-8 text-sm italic text-muted-foreground">Costs, values, and repair outcomes vary based on device condition, parts availability, and market demand.</p></div></section><section id="comparisons" class="border-t border-border py-10 md:py-14"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Compare iPhone XR to Other Models</h2><p class="mb-6 text-muted-foreground">Side-by-side comparisons to help you decide whether to repair, keep, or upgrade. These guides are being published progressively as part of our ongoing device reference series.</p><div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2"><div class="flex items-center rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-medium">iPhone XR vs iPhone 11</span><span class="ml-auto text-xs italic">Coming soon</span></div><div class="flex items-center rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-medium">iPhone XR vs iPhone XS</span><span class="ml-auto text-xs italic">Coming soon</span></div><div class="flex items-center rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-medium">iPhone XR vs iPhone 12</span><span class="ml-auto text-xs italic">Coming soon</span></div><div class="flex items-center rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 text-muted-foreground"><span class="font-medium">iPhone XR vs iPhone SE (2020)</span><span class="ml-auto text-xs italic">Coming soon</span></div></div></div></section><section id="faqs" class="border-t border-border py-14 md:py-20"><div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4"><h2 class="mb-10 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl">Frequently Asked Questions About the iPhone XR</h2><div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-card shadow-sm"><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>How long will the iPhone XR be supported?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">The iPhone XR received its last major iOS update with iOS 18. Apple may continue to issue limited security patches for iOS 18, but the device will not receive iOS 19 or later. App compatibility will gradually decline as developers target newer iOS versions. Source: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/guide/iphone/iphe3fa5df43/ios" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple</a>.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>Can I still use my iPhone XR in 2026?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">Yes. The iPhone XR remains functional for calls, messaging, browsing, email, and most social media in 2026. Where users may notice limitations is in newer app requirements, low-light photography, and multitasking with demanding applications. For many use cases — especially as a secondary device — it remains capable.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>What iOS version can the iPhone XR update to?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">The iPhone XR supports up to iOS 18. It cannot be updated to iOS 19, iOS 26, or any subsequent release. Apple may still issue minor security patches for iOS 18 on a limited basis. Source: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/guide/iphone/iphe3fa5df43/ios" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple iOS compatibility</a>.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>What happens when an iPhone is no longer supported?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">The device continues to work, but it stops receiving new features and, eventually, security updates. Over time, app developers drop support for older iOS versions — starting with banking, payment, and security-sensitive apps. The phone doesn't become unusable, but its utility narrows over a period of 1–3 years after losing major iOS support.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>Is the iPhone XR worth fixing?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">For single-issue repairs like a worn battery or cracked screen, repair is typically worthwhile if the device meets your software needs. For multiple simultaneous failures (screen + back glass + battery), the combined cost often approaches the device's market value, making replacement a more practical option.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>When should you upgrade from an iPhone XR?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">The clearest signal to upgrade is when the apps you rely on daily stop supporting your iOS version — particularly banking, transit, and authentication apps. If you're not hitting those limits and the device is physically functional, there's no urgency to upgrade. It's a personal decision based on your needs.</div></div></details><details class="group border-b border-border last:border-b-0"><summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-secondary/50 [&amp;::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden"><span>What is the resale value of an iPhone XR today?</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-0"><div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&amp;_a]:text-primary [&amp;_a]:underline [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-2">Resale value depends heavily on condition, battery health, storage capacity, and carrier lock status. Cash trade-in values are typically lower than store credit offers. Market values change frequently with new device releases. For a current estimate based on your specific device, use a <a href="/trade-in">condition-based valuation tool</a>.</div></div></details></div><div class="mt-10 flex it